 means the glue holding my body together is failing. All of my joints will dislocate at the drop of a hat, but it's the worst in my hands. Worst hands my specialist has seen! Gold star! I'm genuinely useless without these, I can't even type or use my mouse without hurting myself. And there are still a lot of things I can't do even with the splints, like use a pen for more than a sentence or two. I managed to teach myself how to continue knitting, since I developed a way to do it without needing to grip. I can't do it for long periods, though, so it's a nice little treat, not something I can marathon. They're gonna keep getting worse, though, so at some point -likely sooner rather than later- I'll lose that too. All I can do is my best, but I've taught myself that my best is good enough.

I try to look on the bright side. All I've ever wanted to do is write, and between these bad boys and my light keyswitches, I can still type for a few hours at a time. Means I still get to enjoy my passion, at least for now.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pBBe05R</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[MisterTeatime]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>MRW I hear Happy Gilmore 2 is happening and Shooter McGavin will be returning!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/DACP7fG</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/c9mKEdI.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Source: Happy Gilmore (1996) #IntergalacticQualityGifs (Check WiFi) 

